{{wiktionary|Athene}} '''[[Athene]]''' or Athena is the shrewd companion of heroes and the goddess of heroic endeavour in Greek mythology.
'''Athene''' may also refer to: *[[881 Athene]], a main-belt asteroid *[[Athene (bird)|''Athene'' (bird)]], a genus of small owls *[[Athene (Cynuria)]], a town in ancient Cynuria, Greece *[[Athene Glacier]], a glacier in Antarctica *[[HMS Athene|HMS ''Athene'']], an aircraft transport *[[USS Athene (AKA-22)|USS ''Athene'' (AKA-22)]], an ''Artemis''-class attack cargo ship *[[Bachir Boumaaza]] or Athene (born 1980), Belgian YouTube personality and social activist *[[Athene (research center)]], stylized as ATHENE, an IT security research institute in Darmstadt, Germany
